Rating: 4
Made this for the first time last night, not a fan of boiled potatoes so I cut the potatoes in half, tossed in olive oil with salt and pepper and laid flat on a rimmed cookie sheet at 425 for 20 minutes and flipped for about another 15 minutes, everything else was the same except I used a regular cucumber as I couldn't find the pickling kind. I made the dish about 3 to 4 hours ahead and brought to room temp, everyone raved about them and there were no leftovers. I will definitely make again.

